&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neros is a defense technology company rebuilding America’s drone industrial base. We design and manufacture high-performance unmanned systems that are tested in combat, iterated at startup speed, and built at massive scale. Our team culture is fast, hands-on, and obsessed with closing the gap between design and deployment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As drones transform the character of warfare, Neros is delivering the systems the West needs to compete on the modern battlefield and deter the adversaries of democracy. We’re hiring engineers, operators, and builders who want to move fast, take on extreme ownership, and get capability into the hands of warfighters in months, not years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will be doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an early Neros employee, you will get to help decide the direction of our future. Our Accountant will support accounting processes for a Ukrainian LLC (ТОВ) in collaboration with an outsourced accounting provider.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage payroll-related processes, including invoice handling and coordination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with financial documentation and reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and analyze&amp;nbsp;P&amp;amp;L (Profit &amp;amp; Loss)&amp;nbsp;statements, track key financial metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in&amp;nbsp;aligning Ukrainian accounting/reporting with global financial processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support integration of&amp;nbsp;local reporting into NetSuite (or&amp;nbsp;Quick books etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should have the following&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;English level:&amp;nbsp;Upper-Intermediate (B2+) or&amp;nbsp;higher&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of&amp;nbsp;Ukrainian accounting and reporting standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with&amp;nbsp;P&amp;amp;L management and financial analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to&amp;nbsp;detail and ability to&amp;nbsp;work independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide support for FOP accounting or&amp;nbsp;help organize this function if&amp;nbsp;relevant expertise is&amp;nbsp;available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with outsourced accounting teams is&amp;nbsp;a&amp;nbsp;plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neros is a defense technology company rebuilding America’s drone industrial base. We design and manufacture high-performance unmanned systems that are tested in combat, iterated at startup speed, and built at massive scale. Our team culture is fast, hands-on, and obsessed with closing the gap between design and deployment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As drones transform the character of warfare, Neros is delivering the systems the West needs to compete on the modern battlefield and deter the adversaries of democracy. We’re hiring engineers, operators, and builders who want to move fast, take on extreme ownership, and get capability into the hands of warfighters in months, not years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will be doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neros is looking for an Advanced Manufacturing Engineer to own the full lifecycle of our peripheral hardware products — from early prototyping through high-volume manufacturing. This is a hands-on, high-ownership role at the intersection of engineering, operations, and quality, where you will be the connective tissue between design and production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Production Readiness Reviews and own the design package as products transition from prototype to full-scale manufacturing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive Design for Manufacturability (DFM) and Design for Testability (DFT) improvements across the product lifecycle to reduce cost, improve yield, and accelerate ramp&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and evolve the Bill of Materials (BOM), proactively identifying and resolving supply chain risks including component obsolescence, alternate sourcing, and shortage mitigation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain quality control processes, working with contract manufacturers and internal teams to define acceptance criteria, inspection protocols, and failure analysis workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage regulatory and compliance requirements (e.g., FCC, CE, RoHS, UL) from design through certification, ensuring products meet all applicable standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the long-term technical owner for released products, supporting sustaining engineering, cost reduction initiatives, and field issue resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with hardware design, firmware, and operations teams to ensure manufacturability and reliability are considered early in the development process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should have the following&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineering or equivalent degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years experience in a hardware production environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;FPV or drone experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solidworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;KiCAD or Altium&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;US Salary Range&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$107,000 -$150,000 USD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The salary range for this role is an estimate based on a wide range of compensation factors, inclusive of base salary only. Actual salary may vary based on (but not limited to) work experience, education and/or training, critical skills, and/or business considerations. Highly competitive equity grants are considered part of Neros&#39; total compensation package.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re an equal opportunity employer. We welcome all applicants without attention to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran or disability status.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neros is a defense technology company rebuilding America’s drone industrial base. We design and manufacture high-performance unmanned systems that are tested in combat, iterated at startup speed, and built at massive scale. Our team culture is fast, hands-on, and obsessed with closing the gap between design and deployment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As drones transform the character of warfare, Neros is delivering the systems the West needs to compete on the modern battlefield and deter the adversaries of democracy. We’re hiring engineers, operators, and builders who want to move fast, take on extreme ownership, and get capability into the hands of warfighters in months, not years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will be doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Mechanical Assembly Technician at Neros, you will be instrumental in the assembly of our drones. Your day to day will consist of working closely with leaders to read, interpret, and execute on work orders. You will also be assembling mechanical systems–from full vehicle structures to installing components,&amp;nbsp; sub-assemblies, and other using other hand-tools such as screwdrivers and tweezers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a highly dynamic role where you will get an opportunity to see a factory being built from the ground up and potentially influence the success of our company. The role will also have opportunities for professional advancement.&amp;nbsp; If you are an organized, detail &amp;amp; process oriented mechanical assembly technician, please apply below.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should have the following&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or equivalency certificate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience with hand or power tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read work instructions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands on experience with mechanical assemblies&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical knowledge of safe work practices such as safe work practices for specific tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to follow written and oral instructions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Part-107 and/or experience flying drones FPV and line of sight&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;US Salary Range&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$20/hr - $35/hr USD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hourly range for this role is an estimate based on a wide range of compensation factors, inclusive of base salary only. Actual salary may vary based on (but not limited to) work experience, education and/or training, critical skills, and/or business considerations. Highly competitive equity grants are considered part of Neros&#39; total compensation package.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re an equal opportunity employer. We welcome all applicants without attention to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran or disability status.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Neros is a defense technology company rebuilding America’s drone industrial base. We design and manufacture high-performance unmanned systems that are tested in combat, iterated at startup speed, and built at massive scale. Our team culture is fast, hands-on, and obsessed with closing the gap between design and deployment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As drones transform the character of warfare, Neros is delivering the systems the West needs to compete on the modern battlefield and deter the adversaries of democracy. We’re hiring engineers, operators, and builders who want to move fast, take on extreme ownership, and get capability into the hands of warfighters in months, not years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will be doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate General Counsel, Product will serve as Neros’ lead product lawyer. Working closely with the General Counsel and CTO, the AGC will guide all of Neros’ interactions with the FCC, NTIA, FAA, and other regulatory stakeholders. The AGC will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As Neros’ principal product attorney, take a solution-oriented approach to supporting the most commercially viable products possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee Neros’ ensure compliance with FTC, NTIA, and FAA regulations, as well as the NDAA and AI legislation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as Neros’ in-house expert on the laws governing radio spectrum usage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the Export Control Officer (ECO) in the ECO’s oversight of ITAR compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer Neros’ IP portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;You should have the following&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;JD and membership in a state bar or the District of Columbia bar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 8 years of experience in government, big-law, or a combination, working on radio spectrum issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience advising defense technology companies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A practical, solution-oriented approach to practicing law&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An ability to translate legal concepts to non-lawyer audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An ability to obtain a Top Secret clearance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A desire to stock the arsenal of democracy and defend the West&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A prior role at the FCC, FAA, NTIA, or a DoW office with spectrum stakeholder status&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-house startup experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team sports experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;US Salary Range&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;$162,500 – $227,500 USD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The salary range for this role is an estimate based on a wide range of compensation factors, inclusive of base salary only. Actual salary may vary based on (but not limited to) work experience, education and/or training, critical skills, and/or business considerations.&amp;nbsp;Highly competitive equity grants are considered art of Neros&#39; total compensation package.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re an equal opportunity employer. We welcome all applicants without attention to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran or disability status&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neros is a defense technology company rebuilding America’s drone industrial base. We design and manufacture high-performance unmanned systems that are tested in combat, iterated at startup speed, and built at massive scale. Our team culture is fast, hands-on, and obsessed with closing the gap between design and deployment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As drones transform the character of warfare, Neros is delivering the systems the West needs to compete on the modern battlefield and deter the adversaries of democracy. We’re hiring engineers, operators, and builders who want to move fast, take on extreme ownership, and get capability into the hands of warfighters in months, not years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will be doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;As the Autonomy Lead, you will own the development of Neros&#39; next autonomy product from the ground up. You&#39;ll lead a small, high-performing team of autonomy engineers while directly driving the software architecture and defining hardware requirements for partner teams to design around. Day-to-day, you&#39;ll be in the code — developing terminal guidance, position hold, visual navigation, and swarming capabilities across current and future Neros platforms. This is a technical leadership role: you&#39;ll set the direction, make the hard calls, and ship capability that gets into soldiers&#39; hands.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the autonomy software development effort for an upcoming Neros product, owning architecture decisions end-to-end&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define hardware requirements and interface closely with hardware teams to ensure software and system design are tightly coupled&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and iterate on terminal guidance, position hold, visual navigation, and swarming capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hire, manage, and grow a small team of autonomy engineers — setting technical standards and maintaining a high execution bar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and review production-quality embedded autonomy code in C, C++, and/or Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate effectively under hardware constraints, making smart tradeoffs between performance and compute/power budgets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should have the following&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years proven experience leading technical work in hardware-constrained autonomy — small drones, ground robots, or similar systems strongly preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on depth in one or more of: computer vision, state estimation, controls, or robotics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing engineers and delivering projects end-to-end, not just contributing to them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency in C, C++, and/or Python in embedded or resource-constrained environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience hiring for autonomy or AI roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior work with quadcopters or other aerospace systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Betaflight, ExpressLRS, or ArduPilot&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;US Salary Range&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$190,000 - $266,000 USD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The salary range for this role is an estimate based on a wide range of compensation factors, inclusive of base salary only. Actual salary may vary based on (but not limited to) work experience, education and/or training, critical skills, and/or business considerations. Highly competitive equity grants are considered part of Neros&#39; total compensation package.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re an equal opportunity employer. We welcome all applicants without attention to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran or disability status.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neros is a defense technology company rebuilding America’s drone industrial base. We design and manufacture high-performance unmanned systems that are tested in combat, iterated at startup speed, and built at massive scale. Our team culture is fast, hands-on, and obsessed with closing the gap between design and deployment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As drones transform the character of warfare, Neros is delivering the systems the West needs to compete on the modern battlefield and deter the adversaries of democracy. We’re hiring engineers, operators, and builders who want to move fast, take on extreme ownership, and get capability into the hands of warfighters in months, not years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will be doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Autonomy Mechatronics Engineer (Hardware &amp;amp; Test), you will own the physical stack that enables autonomy at Neros. You will design, integrate, and test mechanical systems that directly enable autonomous behavior, then prove them under realistic operating conditions. This role spans early-stage concept work through field testing, with direct ownership of both the hardware and the experimental loop. We are looking for engineers who are comfortable moving between CAD, code, in-field testing, and production, and who have demonstrated exceptional ability across the full robotics stack.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own autonomy-critical mechanical subsystems from concept through testing and deployment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and execute test infrastructure and field experiments to validate real-world performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diagnose and resolve cross-disciplinary failures across mechanics, autonomy, sensing, and manufacturing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should have the following&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of professional experience in mechanical engineering, robotics, or mechatronics roles, with direct ownership of shipped hardware systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency in mechanical design and CAD (e.g., SolidWorks, NX, or equivalent), including tolerance analysis and production drawings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience designing and executing hardware test campaigns, including lab, environmental, and field testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to debug complex, cross-disciplinary issues involving mechanical systems, sensors, controls, and embedded software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with rapid prototyping methods (CNC, sheet metal, composites, additive manufacturing) and iterative design cycles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of structural, thermal, or dynamic analysis using FEA or first-principles calculations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with autonomy or robotics systems (UAVs, UGVs, or similar), including an understanding of how mechanical design impacts sensing and control performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting manufacturing and scale-up, including build procedures, fixtures, and collaboration with contract manufacturers or suppliers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Nice to have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience running a test qualification campaign for a robotic or drone product&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience characterizing sensors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;US Salary Range&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$121,000 - $169,500 USD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The salary range for this role is an estimate based on a wide range of compensation factors, inclusive of base salary only. Actual salary may vary based on (but not limited to) work experience, education and/or training, critical skills, and/or business considerations. Highly competitive equity grants are considered part of Neros&#39; total compensation package.&lt;/p&gt;
